<font color="#FF0000">IS ANY BODY OUT THERE?</font><br>
<tt>Thu May  8 23:11:59 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
  Every once in a while,usually on a rainy day and if I have the house to myself,I pop PLATOON or HAMBURGER HILL into the vcr.I sit and watch and remember.The tears flow and I feel like hell for a few days.I guess that some times I feel like I have to remind myself that I was once a warrior and these films are about the only thing around that I can bond to.Most of the friends I've had either skated Nam or had little combat experience,and I've always felt a  <br>
little lost trying to explain that part of my life to others.            Tonight I was reading the local newspaper and there was  an article about this web site.                                                  I served with K Co.,3rd Bn.,9th Marines in I corps from July to Dec. 1966,as a forward observer(f.o.).Prior to that I had spent a year in country as a cannoncocker(105's).I would truly love to hear from anyone who was there with me,especially anyone who was on &quot;operation stars and stripes&quot;,July4-5,1966.
